                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14299729" author="briksoftware" created="Sat, 31 Jan 2015 09:34:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This happens because in Java 1.8.0u25 Oracle change the behavior of CipherInputStream. It used to swallow GeneralSecurityException, which was quite convenient for handling badly formatted PDF. Now it throws an IOException instead. Attached is a patch to catch and ignore this kind of exception, which makes the test document work again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14300273" author="jira-bot" created="Sun, 1 Feb 2015 17:54:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1656341 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lehmi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lehmi&quot;&gt;lehmi&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1656341&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1656341&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2586&quot; title=&quot;IllegalBlockSizeException: Input length must be multiple of 16 when decrypting with padded cipher&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2586&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2586&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: detect and swallow GeneralSecurityException as it used to be done using JVMs &amp;lt; 1.8 as poroposed by Michele Balistreri&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14300276" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 1 Feb 2015 17:59:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve applied the proposed patch with a small addition.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the contribution!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
